    data = get_data(symbol,start_date='2003-09-03',interval="1d")

    data['Year'] = data['Date'].apply(lambda x: x.year)

    data = data.sort_values(['Date'])
    data_monthly = data.groupby(['Year','Month']).apply(lambda df: df.iloc[-1,:])
    data_monthly.index = data_monthly['Date']
    return( 
        data_monthly

Q2:¶

Create a return index time-series of 60% S&P + 40% AGG, rebalanced monthly. Base it at 100 on 30/Sept/2003. [10 points]

  • The formula for calculating continuous return: $r = \ln(p_{t}/p_{t-1})$

  • The formula for calculating portfolio return: (continuous return): $r_p = \ln( w_A * e^{r_A} + w_B * e^{r_B})$

  • The formula for calculating portfolio return: (simple return): $r_p = w_A * r_A + w_B * r_B$

In [ ]:
data_month = data.copy()

# calculate the continuous return: r = log(p_{t}/p_{t-1})
data_month['return_AGG'] = np.log( data_month['close_AGG'] / data_month['close_AGG'].shift()  )
data_month['return_SP'] = np.log( data_month['close_SP'] / data_month['close_SP'].shift() )

# calculate the portfolio return: the weights remain 0.6 and 0.4 repectively, because we assume the portfolio is rebalanced monthly.
data_month['return_40/60'] = np.log( 0.4 * np.exp(data_month['return_AGG']) + 0.6 * np.exp(data_month['return_SP']))

# calculate the index (base at 100 on 30 Sep 2003)
data_month['index_AGG'] = data_month['close_AGG']/data_month['close_AGG'][0] * 100 
data_month['index_SP'] = data_month['close_SP']/data_month['close_SP'][0] * 100 
data_month['index_40/60'] = 100 * np.exp( data_month['return_40/60'].cumsum() )
data_month.loc[data_month.index[0],'index_40/60'] = 100

# show the result
data_month

# Rebalance Process
target_propotion_AGG = 0.4 
target_propotion_SP = 0.6

df = data_rebalance_initial.copy()
for current_date, last_date in zip(df.index[1:], df.index[:-1]):
    # calculate the portfolio asset amount
    df.loc[current_date,'40/60 asset amount'] = (df.loc[last_date,'quantity_AGG'] * df.loc[current_date,'price_AGG'] +  
                                             df.loc[last_date,'quantity_SP'] * df.loc[current_date,'price_SP'] )
    # the weight should be fixed at the same value as target weight
    df.loc[current_date,'weight_AGG'] = target_propotion_AGG
    df.loc[current_date,'weight_SP'] = target_propotion_SP 

    # in order to fix the weight, we need to achieve the corresponding quantity of each asset in the portfolio
    df.loc[current_date,'quantity_AGG'] = df.loc[current_date,'40/60 asset amount'] * df.loc[current_date,'weight_AGG'] / df.loc[current_date,'price_AGG']  
    df.loc[current_date,'quantity_SP'] = df.loc[current_date,'40/60 asset amount'] * df.loc[current_date,'weight_SP'] / df.loc[current_date,'price_SP'] 

    # in order to the realize the quantity we need, we should do some trades 
    df.loc[current_date,'sell/buy_quantity_AGG'] = df.loc[current_date,'quantity_AGG'] - df.loc[last_date,'quantity_AGG']
    df.loc[current_date,'sell/buy_quantity_SP'] = df.loc[current_date,'quantity_SP'] - df.loc[last_date,'quantity_SP']
    
#df['real_weight_AGG'] = df['quantity_AGG'] * df['price_AGG'] / df['40/60 asset amount']

Q3:¶

Calculate the annualised return and volatility of three portfolios, i.e. AGG, S&P, and 60/40, and return correlations between AGG and S&P in the following way [20 points]:

  • First half of the sample and second half of the sample

  • Entire sample period

  • holding-period return: $$ r_h = \frac{P_{end}-P_0}{P_0}$$

  • annulized return: $$ \begin{aligned} P_{end} = P_0 \exp(r \frac{n}{12}) & = P_0 \exp( \sum \limits_{i=1}^{n} r_{i,monthly} 1_{month} ) \\ & =P_0 \exp( \sum \limits_{i=1}^{n} r_{ \text{ i, annulized monthly}} \frac{1}{12} ) \\ r_{ \text{ i, annulized monthly}} & = 12 r_{ \text{ i, monthly}}\\ r & = \frac{1}{n} \sum \limits_{i=1}^{n} r_{\text{ i, annulized monthly}} \end{aligned} $$

  • annulized volatility of monthly return:

$$ \sigma_{\text{yearly}} = \sqrt{12}\sigma_{ \text{monthly}} $$
In [ ]:
# Annualise the return:  exp(r_month* 1 month * 12) = exp(r_year * 1 year)  ==>  r_year = r_month * 12    
def calculate_return_and_volatility(df):
    return([
        # holding perioud return
        (df['close_AGG'][-1] - df['close_AGG'][0]) / df['close_AGG'][0] ,  
        (df['close_SP'][-1] - df['close_SP'][0]) / df['close_SP'][0] ,  
        (df['index_40/60'][-1] - df['index_40/60'][0]) / df['index_40/60'][0] ,  
        '-',
        # annulized holding-period return
        np.nanmean( 12 * df['return_AGG']  ),
        np.nanmean( 12 * df['return_SP'] ),
        np.nanmean( 12 * df['return_40/60'] ),
        '-',
        # volatility
        np.std(df['return_AGG'].dropna(), ddof=1) * np.sqrt(12), 
        np.std(df['return_SP'].dropna(), ddof=1) * np.sqrt(12),
        np.std(df['return_40/60'].dropna(), ddof=1) * np.sqrt(12),  
        '-',
        # correlation
        df[['return_AGG','return_SP']].corr().values[0][1]
    ])

breakpoint = int(data_month.shape[0]/2)  # calculate the breakpoint

data_volatility_for_annul_return = pd.DataFrame(
    {
        'entire sample': calculate_return_and_volatility(data_month),
        'the first half of the sample': calculate_return_and_volatility(data_month[:breakpoint]),
        'the second half of the sample': calculate_return_and_volatility(data_month[breakpoint:])
    },
    index = ['holding_period_return_AGG',
             'holding_period_return_SP',
             'holding_period_return_40/60',
             '-',
             'annulized_return_AGG',
             'annulized_return_SP',
             'annulized_return_40/60',
             '-',
             'annulized volatility of monthly_R_AGG',
             'annulized volatility of monthly_R_SP',
             'annulized volatility of monthly_R_40/60',
             '-',
             'correlation coefficient of monthly_a.R_AGG & monthly_a.R_SP']
)

Q4:¶

Create monthly return distributions of AGG, S&P, and 60/40 portfolios from the entire sample and compare their statistical properties [20 points]

  • Skewness: $$ S = E[(\frac{X-\mu}{\sigma})^3]$$
  • sample skewness: $$ \hat{S} = \frac{1}{n-2}\sum_{i=1}^{n}(\frac{X_i-\hat{\mu}}{ \hat{\sigma}})^3$$
  • Kurtosis: $$ K = E[(\frac{X-\mu}{\sigma})^4] $$
  • excess Kurtosis: $$ K_{excess} = K -3 $$

  • sample skewness: $$ \hat{K} = \frac{1}{n-2}\sum_{i=1}^{n}(\frac{X_i-\hat{\mu}}{ \hat{\sigma}})^4$$

  • $ \hat{\mu} = \bar{X} $

  • $ \hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{1}{n-1}\sum \limits_{i=1}^{n}(X_i - \bar{X})^2 $

Tips: if we want to use np.std(X), make sure we assign the freedom loss. For example, np.std(X, ddof=1)

In [ ]:
# ------- Calculate_moment -------
def calculate_moment(X):
    X = pd.Series(X)
    X = X.dropna() # drop NA
    mu = np.mean(X)
    sigma = np.sqrt(  np.sum( (X - np.mean(X))**2 ) / (  len(X) -1 ) )
    skewness = np.sum( ( (X-mu)/sigma )**3 ) / (  len(X) -2 ) 
    kurtosis = np.sum( ( (X-mu)/sigma )**4 ) / (  len(X) -2 ) # minus 2 freedom 
    excess_kurtosis = kurtosis -3 
    return(pd.Series({
        'count': len(X),
        'mean': mu,
        'std': sigma, # the same as np.std( X, ddof=1 ) 
        'skewness': skewness,
        'kurtosis': kurtosis,
        'excess kurtosis': excess_kurtosis,
        'min': min(X),
        '25%': X.quantile(0.25),
        '50%': X.quantile(0.50),
        '75%': X.quantile(0.75),
        'max': max(X),
    }))

data_statistics_for__return =pd.DataFrame({
    'return_AGG': calculate_moment(data_month['return_AGG']),
    'return_SP': calculate_moment(data_month['return_SP']),
    'return_40/60': calculate_moment(data_month['return_40/60']),
})

Q5:¶

If we had invested $100 in each portfolio, i.e. AGG, S&P, and 60/40, on 30/Sept/2003 and held till 31 Dec 2021, what would have been the largest loss experienced from each investment (i.e. maximum drawdown, aka MDD) and how long would they have taken to recover back to the peak of the assets prior to the MDD (i.e. recovery time back to high watermark)? [20 points]

In [ ]:
# ------- calculate_MDD -------
def calculate_MDD(df,symbol):
    df=df.copy()
    df['date'] = df.index
    df['previous_max'] = df['date'].apply(lambda x: np.max(df[df.index <= x][symbol]) )
    df['previous_max_date'] = df['date'].apply(lambda x: df['date'][np.argmax(df[df.index <= x][symbol])] )
    target_row = np.argmin( (df[symbol] - df['previous_max'])/df['previous_max'] )
    MDD = df['previous_max'][target_row] - df[symbol][target_row]
    MDD_percent = MDD / df['previous_max'][target_row]
    MDD_start_date = df['previous_max_date'][target_row]
    MDD_end_date = df.index[target_row]
    MDD_peak_value = df['previous_max'][target_row]
    MDD_through_value = df[symbol][target_row]
    df_after_MDD = df[ (df.index > MDD_end_date) & ( df[symbol] > MDD_peak_value ) ].copy()
    MDD_recover_date = df_after_MDD['date'][0] if df_after_MDD.shape[0] > 0 else np.NaN
    MDD_recover_value = df.loc[MDD_recover_date, symbol]
    MDD_recover_period = np.NaN if str(MDD_recover_date).lower() == 'nan' else (MDD_recover_date - MDD_end_date) 
    return(pd.Series({
        'MDD': MDD,
        'MDD(%)': f"{MDD_percent: .2%}",
        'MDD_start_date': MDD_start_date,
        'MDD_peak_value': MDD_peak_value,
        'MDD_end_date': MDD_end_date,
        'MDD_through_value': MDD_through_value,
        'MDD_recover_date': MDD_recover_date,
        'MDD_recover_value': MDD_recover_value,
        'MDD_recover_period': MDD_recover_period
    }))

data_MDD_for_return = pd.DataFrame({
    'close_AGG': calculate_MDD(data_month,'close_AGG'),
    'close_SP': calculate_MDD(data_month,'close_SP'),
    'index_40/60': calculate_MDD(data_month,'index_40/60')
})

def plot_decoration(ax, symbol, df = data_MDD_for_return, df_text_info = data_month ): 
    x_MDD_start_point = df.loc['MDD_start_date',symbol]
    y_MDD_start_point = df.loc['MDD_peak_value',symbol]
    x_MDD_end_point = df.loc['MDD_end_date',symbol]
    y_MDD_end_point = df.loc['MDD_through_value',symbol]
    x_MDD_recover_point = df.loc['MDD_recover_date',symbol]
    y_MDD_recover_point = df.loc['MDD_recover_value',symbol]
    MDD = df.loc['MDD',symbol]
    MDD_percentage = df.loc['MDD(%)',symbol]
    period_MDD =  x_MDD_end_point -x_MDD_start_point

    # add scatters
    ax.scatter( [x_MDD_start_point, x_MDD_end_point, x_MDD_recover_point],
                [y_MDD_start_point, y_MDD_end_point, y_MDD_recover_point],
                s=55, c='w', marker='o', edgecolors='r', alpha =0.8  )
    period_recover = x_MDD_recover_point -x_MDD_end_point

    # add annotates on scatters
    ax.annotate(f"{y_MDD_start_point:.2f}",
                  xy=(x_MDD_start_point, y_MDD_start_point),
                  xytext=(-20,+5),
                  fontsize=10,
                  textcoords='offset points') # peak point
    ax.annotate(f"{y_MDD_end_point:.2f}",
                  xy=(x_MDD_end_point, y_MDD_end_point),
                  xytext=(-10,-13),
                  fontsize=10,
                  textcoords='offset points') # through point
    ax.annotate(f"{y_MDD_recover_point:.2f}",
                    xy=(x_MDD_recover_point, y_MDD_recover_point),
                    xytext = (-20,+5),
                    fontsize = 10,
                    textcoords='offset points' )

    # add lines 
    ax.plot([x_MDD_start_point, x_MDD_start_point], [y_MDD_start_point, y_MDD_end_point], 'g--')
    ax.plot([x_MDD_start_point, x_MDD_end_point], [y_MDD_end_point, y_MDD_end_point], 'g--')
    ax.plot([x_MDD_end_point, x_MDD_recover_point], [y_MDD_end_point, y_MDD_end_point], 'r--')
    ax.plot([x_MDD_recover_point, x_MDD_recover_point], [y_MDD_end_point, y_MDD_recover_point], 'r--')

    # add annotates on lines
    ax.annotate(f"MDD",
                  xy=(x_MDD_start_point, (y_MDD_start_point+y_MDD_end_point)/2 ),
                  xytext=(-28,-5),
                  fontsize=10,
                  textcoords='offset points') # through point
    if symbol !='close_AGG': # close_AGG has no recover_point, so we use if-statement here     
        ax.annotate(f"T2",
                  xy=(x_MDD_recover_point, y_MDD_end_point ),
                  xytext=(-15,-13),
                  fontsize=10,
                  textcoords='offset points') # through point
        ax.annotate(f"T1",
                  xy=(x_MDD_start_point, y_MDD_end_point ),
                  xytext=(+5,-13),
                  fontsize=10,
                  textcoords='offset points') # through point
    else: 
        ax.annotate(f"T2",
                  xy=(x_MDD_recover_point, y_MDD_end_point ),
                  xytext=(-30,-13),
                  fontsize=10,
                  textcoords='offset points') # through point
        ax.annotate(f"T1",
                  xy=(x_MDD_start_point, y_MDD_end_point ),
                  xytext=(+40,-13),
                  fontsize=10,
                  textcoords='offset points') # through point

    # add text on the left-top 
    text = ( f"MDD: {np.abs(MDD):.2f} ({MDD_percentage})\n" +
             f"T1 (MDD period): from {x_MDD_start_point.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} to {x_MDD_end_point.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} || ({period_MDD.days} days)\n"  +
             f"T2 (recover period): from {x_MDD_end_point.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} to {x_MDD_recover_point.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')} || ({period_recover.days} days)"
            )
    ax.text(df_text_info.index[0], df_text_info[symbol].max(), 
            verticalalignment = "top", 
            horizontalalignment="left",
            fontsize = 10,
            s=text)

# ------- call functions -------
plot_decoration(ax=axs[0,0], symbol='close_AGG', df=data_MDD_for_return, df_text_info=data_month)
plot_decoration(ax=axs[0,1], symbol='close_SP', df=data_MDD_for_return, df_text_info=data_month)
plot_decoration(ax=axs[1,0], symbol='index_40/60', df=data_MDD_for_return, df_text_info=data_month)

Q6:¶

If we had invested $100 in 60/40 on 30/Sept/2003 and left the investment untouched without rebalancing it back to 60/40, what would be the investment outcome and how does this compare with the monthly rebalanced 60/40 portfolio as seen above? [20 points]

# ------- build the no rebalance portfolio -------
# calculate the quantity
data_month_expend = data_month.copy()
quantity_AGG = 100 * 0.4 / data['close_AGG'][0]
quantity_SP = 100 * 0.6 / data['close_SP'][0]

# calculate the no-rebalance portfolio value
data_month_expend['index_no-rebalance'] = quantity_AGG * data_month_expend['close_AGG'] + quantity_SP* data_month_expend['close_SP']

# calculate the weight
data_month_expend['weight_AGG'] = (quantity_AGG * data_month_expend['close_AGG']) / data_month_expend['index_no-rebalance']
data_month_expend['weight_SP'] =  (quantity_SP * data_month_expend['close_SP']) / data_month_expend['index_no-rebalance']

# calculate the return of no-rebalance portfolio 
data_month_expend['return_no-rebalance'] = np.log( data_month_expend['weight_AGG'].shift(1) * np.exp(data_month_expend['return_AGG']) +
                                                   data_month_expend['weight_SP'].shift(1) * np.exp(data_month_expend['return_SP']) )
